{"id":8586,"date":"2025-09-22T11:06:08","date_gmt":"2025-09-22T11:06:08","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/realtrips.in\/?post_type=trip&#038;p=8586"},"modified":"2025-12-04T11:50:17","modified_gmt":"2025-12-04T11:50:17","slug":"kedarnath-chopta-tungnath","status":"publish","type":"trip","link":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/trip\/kedarnath-chopta-tungnath\/","title":{"rendered":"KEDARNATH CHOPTA TUNGNATH"},"content":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":8834,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","template":"","destination":[104],"activities":[],"trip_types":[75],"difficulty":[],"trip_tag":[],"wptravelengine_custom_taxonomy_tripcategory":[77],"class_list":["post-8586","trip","type-trip","status-publish","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","destination-special-adventure-tours","trip_types-customized-domestic-tour","tripcategory-customized-domestic-tour"],"packages_ids":[8587],"trip_extras":[],"cut_off_time":{"enabled":false,"duration":0,"duration_unit":"days"},"booked-seats":[],"code":"WTE-8586","price":18777,"has_sale":false,"sale_price":0,"discount_percent":0,"currency":{"code":"INR","symbol":"&#8377;"},"duration":{"days":5,"nights":4,"duration_unit":"days","duration_type":"days"},"min_pax":1,"max_pax":"","discount_value":0,"discount_label":"&#8377;0 Off","primary_category":27,"available_times":{"type":"default","items":["2021-1-01","2021-2-01","2021-3-01","2021-4-01","2021-5-01","2021-6-01","2021-7-01","2021-8-01","2021-9-01","2021-10-01","2021-11-01","2021-12-01"]},"description":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Embark on a soul-stirring adventure that blends <strong>spirituality, trekking, and Himalayan beauty<\/strong> with the Kedarnath\u2013Chopta\u2013Tungnath tour. Begin your journey at <strong>Kedarnath<\/strong>, one of the twelve Jyotirlingas and a major Char Dham pilgrimage site, nestled in the lap of the Garhwal Himalayas. The trek to Kedarnath offers not only devotion but also mesmerizing views of snow-capped peaks and alpine landscapes. Continue to <strong>Chopta<\/strong>, often called the \u201cMini Switzerland of India,\u201d a serene hill station surrounded by meadows and forests, ideal for camping and nature walks. From Chopta, trek to <strong>Tungnath<\/strong>, the highest Shiva temple in the world, and further ascend to <strong>Chandrashila Peak<\/strong> for a breathtaking 360\u00b0 panorama of Himalayan ranges including Nanda Devi, Trishul, and Chaukhamba. This tour is a perfect combination of <strong>pilgrimage, adventure, and natural beauty<\/strong>, offering an unforgettable experience for both devotees and adventure enthusiasts.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->","cost_includes":" 3 star premium hotel stay\n All transfers and sightseeing by AC Vehicle\n Breakfast, Dinner, Lunch\n Toll Tax\n Parking\n Driver Allowance\nTravel Goodies\n 24 x 7 On tour Assistance\n All cost from EX Destination","cost_excludes":"Any meals other than those mentioned above in inclusions\n Airfare \/ Train Ticket\n GST 5%\n All monument entry Fees\n Any portage at airports and hotels, tips, insurance, wine, mineral water, telephone charges, and all items of personal nature\n Any services not specifically mentioned in the inclusions\nEntrance fees to Monuments & other sightseeing points\nExpenses caused by factors beyond our control like rail and flight delays, roadblocks, vehicle malfunctions, political disturbances, etc.\nAnything not mentioned in inclusions","itineraries":[],"faqs":[{"title":"1. What is the ideal duration of this trip? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A 6 to 7-day itinerary is recommended to cover Kedarnath, Chopta, and Tungnath comfortably.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"2. How difficult is the Kedarnath trek? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Kedarnath trek is about 16\u201318 km from Gaurikund, with a moderate difficulty level. Ponies, palkis, and helicopter services are also available.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"3. Why is Kedarnath significant? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Kedarnath is one of the Char Dhams and a Jyotirlinga of Lord Shiva, making it a very important Hindu pilgrimage site.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"4. What is special about Chopta? ","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Chopta is called the \u201cMini Switzerland of India\u201d, known for its scenic meadows, pine forests, and as the base for the Tungnath\u2013Chandrashila trek.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"},{"title":"5. Why is Tungnath famous?","content":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tungnath is the highest Shiva temple in the world (3,680 m), and trekking further to Chandrashila offers spectacular Himalayan views.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->"}],"is_featured":false,"featured_image":{"width":374,"height":226,"file":"2025\/09\/kedarnath-chopta-tungnath-2.png","filesize":181881,"sizes":{"medium":{"file":"kedarnath-chopta-tungnath-2-300x181.png","width":300,"height":181,"filesize":98393,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/kedarnath-chopta-tungnath-2-300x181.png"},"thumbnail":{"file":"kedarnath-chopta-tungnath-2-150x150.png","width":150,"height":150,"filesize":45361,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/kedarnath-chopta-tungnath-2-150x150.png"},"blog-sidebar-size":{"file":"kedarnath-chopta-tungnath-2-100x100.png","width":100,"height":100,"filesize":22264,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/kedarnath-chopta-tungnath-2-100x100.png"},"blog-sidebar-size-thumb":{"file":"kedarnath-chopta-tungnath-2-90x80.png","width":90,"height":80,"filesize":16432,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/kedarnath-chopta-tungnath-2-90x80.png"},"blog-post-two":{"file":"kedarnath-chopta-tungnath-2-342x226.png","width":342,"height":226,"filesize":149626,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/kedarnath-chopta-tungnath-2-342x226.png"},"travolo-related-post-size":{"file":"kedarnath-chopta-tungnath-2-270x226.png","width":270,"height":226,"filesize":121667,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/kedarnath-chopta-tungnath-2-270x226.png"},"blog-post-pagination":{"file":"kedarnath-chopta-tungnath-2-80x80.png","width":80,"height":80,"filesize":14792,"mime_type":"image\/png","source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/kedarnath-chopta-tungnath-2-80x80.png"},"full":{"file":"kedarnath-chopta-tungnath-2.png","width":374,"height":226,"source_url":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/09\/kedarnath-chopta-tungnath-2.png"}},"image_meta":{"aperture":"0","credit":"","camera":"","caption":"","created_timestamp":"0","copyright":"","focal_length":"0","iso":"0","shutter_speed":"0","title":"","orientation":"0","keywords":[]}},"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/trip\/8586","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/trip"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/trip"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=8586"}],"version-history":[{"count":1,"href":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/trip\/8586\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":8594,"href":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/trip\/8586\/revisions\/8594"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/realtrips.thefuturecity.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/8834"}],"wp:atta